From: Brandon Thompson <brandon.joseph.thompson@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 12:39:22 -0700
Subject: Patch: scroll over the sound status icon to adjust volume.

The status cluster's volume glyph only opened the mixer on click; a
wheel anywhere else on the bare bar band already nudges the sink
volume (Bar.qml's nudgeVolume), but the icon's own MouseArea absorbed
wheel events without forwarding them. Give it the same onWheel handling
BarModule already uses for the media pill, so scrolling right over the
glyph works too.

diff --git a/ryoku/shell/quickshell/pill/BarStatus.qml b/ryoku/shell/quickshell/pill/BarStatus.qml
index 62a52b8f..1e36773f 100644
--- a/ryoku/shell/quickshell/pill/BarStatus.qml
+++ b/ryoku/shell/quickshell/pill/BarStatus.qml
@@ -68,6 +68,12 @@ Grid {
             anchors.fill: parent
             cursorShape: Qt.PointingHandCursor
             onClicked: status.open("mixer", volIcon)
+            onWheel: (w) => {
+                if (!volIcon.sink || !volIcon.sink.audio)
+                    return;
+                volIcon.sink.audio.muted = false;
+                volIcon.sink.audio.volume = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, volIcon.vol + (w.angleDelta.y > 0 ? 1 : -1) * 0.03));
+            }
         }
     }
 
